com.bluegosling.collections.immutable

Class AbstractImmutableList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • com.bluegosling.collections.immutable.AbstractImmutableList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of element in the collection
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, List<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractLinkedImmutableList, AmtPersistentList

    public abstract class AbstractImmutableList<E>
extends AbstractList<E>
    An abstract base class for implementing immutable lists. This overrides all mutable methods with final implementations that throw UnsupportedOperationException.

    As with its superclass, AbstractList, the implementations for many operations rely on random access. If implementing an immutable list based on a linked structure (a la LinkedList), consider sub-classing AbstractLinkedImmutableList instead.

    See Also:
    AbstractLinkedImmutableList
